  "prompt": "What were the major events that happened in 2005?",
  "response": "2005 was a significant year with a mix of devastating natural disasters, political shifts, and cultural milestones. Here are some of the major events:\n\n**Natural Disasters:**\n\n*   **Hurricane Katrina (August):** This was arguably the most significant event of the year. The catastrophic hurricane devastated the U.S. Gulf Coast, particularly New Orleans, Louisiana. The disaster led to widespread flooding, loss of life, and a slow and controversial recovery effort.\n*   **Pakistan Earthquake (October):** A powerful earthquake struck Pakistan-administered Kashmir and surrounding areas, killing tens of thousands and leaving millions homeless.\n\n**Politics & International Relations:**\n\n*   **London Bombings (July):** Terrorist bombings targeted London's public transport system, killing 52 people and injuring hundreds.\n*   **Withdrawal of Syrian Troops from Lebanon (April):** Following years of occupation, Syria withdrew its troops from Lebanon, a significant political shift in the region.\n*   **Angela Merkel Becomes German Chancellor (November):** Angela Merkel was inaugurated as the first female Chancellor of Germany.\n*   **Ellen Johnson Sirleaf Elected President of Liberia (November):** Sirleaf became the first female president of an African nation.\n*   **Kyoto Protocol Enters Into Force (February):** An international agreement linked to the United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change, commits its Parties by setting internationally binding emission reduction targets.\n\n**Technology & Culture:**\n\n*   **YouTube Launches (February):** The video-sharing platform YouTube was launched, revolutionizing how people consume and share video content.\n*   **Lance Armstrong Wins 7th Tour de France (July):** Although his titles would later be revoked, Armstrong won his record-breaking seventh consecutive Tour de France title.\n*   **Harry Potter and the Half-Blood Prince Released (July):** The sixth book in the popular Harry Potter series was published and quickly became a bestseller.\n*   **Batman Begins Released (June):** The reboot of the Batman film franchise, directed by Christopher Nolan.\n\n**Other Notable Events:**\n\n*   **Live 8 Concerts (July):** A series of benefit concerts were held around the world to raise awareness about poverty in Africa.\n*   **Creation of the Special Tribunal for Lebanon (March):** An international tribunal was established to investigate the assassination of former Lebanese Prime Minister Rafik Hariri.\n\nThis list isn't exhaustive, but it covers some of the most prominent events of 2005 across various domains. These events had a lasting impact and continue to shape our world today.\n",
